        "title": "feat(ui): per-agent ElevenLabs Voice/TTS settings in control-ui",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a Voice/TTS card to the Control UI agent overview tab, enabling per-agent ElevenLabs TTS configuration directly from the settings modal.\n\n### Features\n- **Enable/disable TTS** per agent (reflects runtime `auto` mode precedence over deprecated `enabled` boolean)\n- **TTS provider selection** (Inherit default / ElevenLabs / OpenAI / Microsoft)\n- **ElevenLabs API key** — password field, SecretRef-aware (renders read-only when backed by SecretRef)\n- **Voice ID** input\n- **Model selector** dropdown\n\n### Implementation\n\nThe `resolveAgentTts` resolver mirrors the runtime `resolveEffectiveTtsConfig` contract from `src/tts/tts-config.ts`:\n- **Deep-merges** TTS config layers: `messages.tts` (base) → `agents.defaults.tts` → `agents.list[].tts` (entry) using a recursive `deepMergeDefined` that preserves nested provider fields (apiKey, model, voice) from inheritance layers unless explicitly overridden\n- **Auto mode**: reads `auto` field first (`always`/`off`/`session`), falls back to deprecated `enabled` boolean\n- **SecretRef detection**: `isSecretRefObject()` checks credential-backed API keys; renders disabled read-only field instead of allowing object-to-string coercion\n- **Model ID**: writes `providers.elevenlabs.modelId` (runtime path), reads `modelId` with `model` fallback for backwards compat\n\n### Files changed\n- `ui/src/ui/views/agents-panels-overview.ts` — `AgentTtsConfig` type, `resolveAgentTts()` helper, Voice/TTS card template\n- `ui/src/ui/views/agents.ts` — 5 new TTS handler props\n- `ui/src/ui/app-render.ts` — TTS handler implementations using `ensureAgentIndex` + `updateConfigFormValue`\n- `ui/src/i18n/locales/en.ts` + 18 locale files — voice/TTS i18n strings\n- `ui/src/styles/components.css` — toggle-switch CSS\n- `ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts` — TTS render tests including SecretRef read-only + conditional fields regression\n\n### Verification\n\n- ✅ Build: `pnpm build` clean (924 modules, 0 errors)\n- ✅ Tests: 12/12 agent tests pass (including SecretRef read-only + ElevenLabs conditional fields regression)\n- ✅ i18n: 11/11 structural alignment tests pass across all 19 locales\n- ✅ Deployed locally to control-ui dist\n\n### ClawSweeper P1 fixes (commit b05c564)\n\n1. **Deep-merge nested TTS provider overrides** — `resolveAgentTts` now uses recursive `deepMergeDefined` (mirroring runtime `deepMergeDefined` from `src/tts/tts-config.ts:25`) instead of top-level key replacement. Inherited `providers.elevenlabs.{apiKey, model, speakerVoiceId}` are preserved when an agent override only sets some fields.\n2. **Reflect TTS auto mode** — enable switch now reads `auto` field first (`always`/`off`/`session`), falling back to `enabled` boolean only when `auto` is absent. Configs with `auto: \"always\"` render as enabled; `auto: \"off\"` renders as disabled.\n\nCommit: `b05c564ac4` on `feature/elevenlabs-voice-settings`\n\n### Screenshots\n\nControl UI agent overview with Voice/TTS card:\n\n![Agent overview with Voice/TTS card](control-ui-agents.png)",
